KZN Premier Senzo Mchunu has resigned from his position on Monday. Senzo Mchunu&#8217;s resignation follows a week long speculation that he was pushed by the new ANC Provincial leadership to resign.According to eNCA reports, Mchunu is accused of defying ANC Provincial leadership on matters regarding government decisions. His cabinet is also accused of failing education in the province which resulted in bad matric results for 2015 matric.Premier Mchunu did not show up at two events he was scheduled to attend over the weekend, fuelling speculation that he was on his way out. comments